<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1921-07-11T03:34:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1921-07-11T03:34:00-05:00" n="685" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d685">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">861.00/8799: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Consul at Harbin</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Jenkins</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Harbin</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1921-07-11T17:00:00+08:26"><hi rend="italic">July 11,
                                        1921—5 p.m.</hi></date><lb/>[Received July 11—3:25
                                p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>Semenoff who is now established at Grodekovo is endeavoring arrange for
                            transportation his troops through Manchuria to Trans-Baikal. If
                            successful this could only result in renewal lawless seizures
                            merchandise and general disorganization of communication with
                            Trans-Baikal. Believe Chinese authorities should be urged not permit
                            Semenoff troops pass through Manchuria.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Jenkins</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>